description: {"blocks":[{"key":"ckch5","text":"Paraffin sections (4mm thickness) of formalin-fixed mouse pancreases were treated with heat/citrate buffer for antigen retrieval. CD44 core proteins were detected immunohistochemically using rat anti-mouse CD44 mAb (IM7 mAb; BD Biosciences) or mouse anti-human CD44v3 mAb (CD44v3: R\u0026D Systems), with horseradish peroxidase-conjugated rabbit anti-rat Ig (Dako) or rabbit anti-mouse Ig (Dako). Background staining was checked using the corresponding isotype control Ig instead of the primary antibody. 3-amino-9-ethylcarbazole (AEC) was used as the chromogen. For morphometry, stained sections were imaged using a light microscope with attached camera (Olympus BX41). Image J software with color deconvolution plugin was used for the quantitative analysis of the % of islet area stained.","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"b6ec3","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
guidelines: {"blocks":[{"key":"b7h3i","text":"Rat anti-mouse CD44 (IM7) mAb recognises all CD44 isoforms (1-4)and mouse anti-human CD44v3 mAb recognises a CD44 isoform that carries HS side-chains (1-3). In mouse pancreas we have demonstrated that these two mAbs have a similar pattern of intra-islet staining.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"8r040","text":"","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"a6eri","text":"References:","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]},{"key":"g43e","text":" 1. steps.step: {"blocks":[{"key":"el8ko","text":"Deparaffinize slides in each xylene for 1 min. rehydrate slides in graded alcohols beginning in absolute ethanol (10 dips)/ container of absolute ethanol), followed by 90% ethanol (10 dips) and 70% ethanol (10 dips).Wash well in running tap water for 5 min.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"40h22","text":"Wipe around sections with a tissue, encircle the sections using a diamond pencil and place in a slide container of tap water (250 ml).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ab6hr","text":"Block endogenous peroxidase activity by incubating sections in 3% hydrogen peroxide in methanol (25 ml 30% H2O2 + 225 ml methanol).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":108,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":110,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"12uhk","text":"Wash 2 x 2 min in 250 ml phosphate-buffered saline (PBS) followed by wash in running tap water for 5 min.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"a3ehu","text":"Prepare citrate buffer, pH 6 for antigen retrieval. Dissolve 1.05 g Citric acid in 500 ml deionized waterand pH using 2 - 10 M NaOH.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7d506","text":"Transfer slides to 250ml citrate buffer and heat in microwave (1600 watt) for 2 min on High power followed by 2 x 6 min on Low power.Allow the slides to cool on the bench for 30 min. Wash slides in 250 ml PBS, 3 x 10 min.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2ts6d","text":"Wipe around sections using tissue. To block non-specific binding of Ig, apply animal free block (diluted to 20% v/v with deionized water) to tissue sections and incubate for 10 min at room temperature.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"90qv3","text":"Tip off excess block in Step 8, wipe around sections using tissue and incubate with 40 μg/ml anti-CD44 (IM7) mAb (or 40 μg/ml rat IgG2bκ as isotype control; diluted in M.O.M. diluent), 125-150 μl/section at room temperature for 1 hour. Alternatively use 10 μg/ml mouse anti-human CD44v3 mAb (or 10 μg/ml mouse IgG2bκas isotype control Ig.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":133,"length":3},{"style":"sub","offset":313,"length":3}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"corg4","text":"Note: For human pancreas specimens, use 12.5 μg/ml  mouse anti-human CD44v3 mAb or 12.5  μg/ml  mouse IgG2bκ as isotype control","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":105,"length":3}],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"7uh87","text":"Wash off primary antibody with PBS and transfer slides to slide container with 250 ml PBS. Wash 2 x 2min.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"6fu9k","text":"Wipe around sections using tissue and incubate with 26-54 μg/ml secondary HRP-rabbit anti-rat Ig (Dako) or alternative 30-60 μg/ml HRP-rabbit anti-rat IgG (Sigma). For use with primary CD44v3 mAb, incubate with 8 μg/ml secondary HRP-rabbit anti-mouse IgG (Invitrogen).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"mhlo","text":"Note: for human pancreas sections, use 6.4 μg/ml secondary HRP-rabbit anti-mouse IgG (invitrogen).","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}},{"key":"789qs","text":"","type":"align-justify","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":{}}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"4ioj9","text":"Wash off secondary antibody with PBS and transfer to slide container with 250 ml PBS. Wash slides 2 x 2min. ","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"fuci1","text":"Prepare AEC working solution: 4.75 ml acetate buffer (see Guidelines), 0.25ml AEC stock solution and 25 μl 3% H2O2. Filter using a disposable 0.2 μm filter. Use within 2 hours of preparation, refrigerate for short-term storage. Protect from light.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[{"style":"sub","offset":111,"length":1},{"style":"sub","offset":113,"length":1}],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"bkorc","text":"Wipe around sections using tissue and cover the sections with AEC solution for 30 min at room temperature.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"2ecsa","text":"Wash off AEC solution with deionized water and transfer slides to slide container with 250 ml deionized water. Wash 3x in 10 min.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"9fnbd","text":"Lightly counterstain with Gill’s hematoxylin, wash in deionized water (2 x) and briefly dip in ammonium water (100 μl ammonia in 250 ml deionized water), 2 x 2 sec. Wash in deionized water (2x in 250 ml) and coverslip using glycergel mounting medium.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}

{"blocks":[{"key":"ffbl1","text":"Image sections using a light microscope with camera attachment. Use Image J software with color deconvolution plugin to determine % of islet area stained.","type":"unstyled","depth":0,"inlineStyleRanges":[],"entityRanges":[],"data":[]}],"entityMap":{}}
